column4: EU to intervene in Microsoft's U.S. Supreme Court data protection case
column5: BRUSSELS The European Union is to make a submission to the U.S. Supreme Court in its hearing of the U.S. Department of Justice's appeal  against a ruling which prevented prosecutors from gaining access to emails held by Microsoft in Ireland.

column4: CORRECTED (OFFICIAL)-Blockchain network IOTA teams up with Microsoft  others on data marketplace
column5: NEW YORK  Nov 28 IOTA  an open-source blockchain network  has teamed up with some of the biggest global corporate names led by Microsoft  Volkswagen and Samsung Group to launch what is aimed to be a secure marketplace for data  IOTA co-founder David Sønstebø said on Tuesday.
